               <p>WILLIAM BOADMAN. I am a <rs id="t18180909-298-viclabel1640" type="occupation">tobacconist</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18180909-298-victim2067 t18180909-298-viclabel1640"></join>, and live at Wapping. On the 5th of August I left my pictures and carpet at Hucks's. I never authorized the prisoner to call for them. The painting was a chesnut cart-house.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18180909-298-person2068">
                  JAMES 
                  HUCKS
               <interp inst="t18180909-298-person2068" type="surname" value="HUCKS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18180909-298-person2068" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18180909-298-person2068" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I keep the Anchor and Hope, public-house, at Shadwell-these things were landed at my house for the prosecutor; the prisoner was in the prosecutor's company at the time, and Boadman was hiring him to take them to his house. I told the prosecutor he might leave them at my house, which he did. Between five and six o'clock in the evening, the prisoner came again, and said he was sent for them - I delivered them to him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18180909-298-person2069">
                  GEORGE 
                  WILLIAM KNIGHT
               <interp inst="t18180909-298-person2069" type="surname" value="WILLIAM KNIGHT"></interp>
